                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-green-800 mb-2 font-medium">Highest Priority</p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-1">
                            <li>Registered Nurses</li>
                            <li>Licensed Practical Nurses</li>
                            <li>Health Care Assistants</li>
                            <li>Medical Laboratory Technicians</li>
                            <li>Pharmacy Technicians</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="bg-purple-50 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-purple-100">
                        <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
                            <span class="text-2xl mr-3">üë∂</span>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-purple-900 m-0">Childcare</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-purple-800 mb-2 font-medium">Targeted Priority</p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-1">
                            <li>Early Childhood Educators</li>
                            <li>ECE Assistants</li>
                            <li>Requires valid ECE certificate from BC</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="bg-amber-50 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-amber-100">
                        <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
                            <span class="text-2xl mr-3">üèóÔ∏è</span>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-amber-900 m-0">Construction</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 mb-2 font-medium">Growing Priority</p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-1">
                            <li>Requires Skilled Trades BC certification</li>
                            <li>Electricians, Plumbers, Carpenters</li>
                            <li>Construction Project Managers</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-blue-100">
                        <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
                            <span class="text-2xl mr-3">üíª</span>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-blue-900 m-0">Tech Sector</h4>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 mb-2 font-medium">Ongoing Priority</p>
                        <ul class="text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-1">
                            <li>Software Engineers</li>
                            <li>Data Scientists</li>
                            <li>DevOps Engineers</li>
                            <li>29 eligible tech occupations</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h2>Alternative Pathway #4: Other Provincial Programs</h2>

                <p>
                    If BC PNP isn't viable for your situation, other provinces offer graduate-friendly pathways that may work for you. While this means relocating outside BC, it could accelerate your PR timeline significantly.
                </p>

                <h3>Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program (OINP)</h3>
                <p>
                    Ontario's Masters Graduate and PhD Graduate streams don't require job offers. If you're willing to study a Master's or PhD in Ontario, these streams offer relatively straightforward paths to nomination.
                </p>

                <h3>Saskatchewan Immigrant Nominee Program (SINP)</h3>
                <p>
                    The SINP International Skilled Worker category has lower minimum score requirements and often processes applications faster than BC. Saskatchewan particularly welcomes healthcare workers and skilled tradespeople.
                </p>

                <h3>Atlantic Immigration Program (AIP)</h3>
                <p>
                    The four Atlantic provinces (New Brunswick, Newfoundland and Labrador, Nova Scotia, Prince Edward Island) participate in the AIP. With a job offer from a designated employer, you can access a streamlined pathway to PR with no Express Entry involvement.
                </p>

                <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-400 p-4 my-6 not-prose rounded-r-xl">
                    <p class="font-bold text-yellow-800 text-sm uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">
                        Provincial Strategy
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-yellow-900 font-medium">
                        The Rural and Northern Immigration Pilot (RNIP) includes communities like Vernon, BC. If you're open to smaller cities, this pilot offers PR pathways with community support and lower competition than urban programs.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <h2>Critical PGWP Considerations for 2026</h2>

                <p>
                    Your Post-Graduation Work Permit is the bridge between student status and PR. Protecting and maximizing your PGWP is essential for any PR strategy.
                </p>

                <h3>PGWP Changes Taking Effect</h3>

                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Program Eligibility:</strong> Starting early 2026, 178 programs will no longer qualify for PGWP eligibility. Verify your program's status before enrolling.</li>
                    <li><strong>Duration Rules:</strong> Programs under 2 years receive PGWPs matching program length. Only programs of 2 years or more receive 3-year PGWPs.</li>
                    <li><strong>Field of Study Requirements:</strong> Certain fields now required for PGWP eligibility in some program types.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Maximizing Your PGWP Time</h3>

                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Start Working Immediately:</strong> Begin accumulating Canadian work experience as soon as your PGWP is approved. Every month counts toward CEC eligibility.</li>
                    <li><strong>Target Skilled Positions:</strong> Ensure your job is in NOC TEER 0-3. Restaurant servers (TEER 4) or retail associates (TEER 5) don't count toward most PR pathways.</li>
                    <li><strong>Document Everything:</strong> Keep pay stubs, tax returns, employment letters, and contracts. You'll need comprehensive proof of your work experience.</li>
                    <li><strong>Apply Early:</strong> Don't wait until your PGWP expires. Submit your PR application with several months of validity remaining.</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Step-by-Step Action Plan for Students</h2>

                <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-2xl mb-6 not-prose border border-slate-200">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Your 2026 PR Strategy Timeline</h4>
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <div class="flex items-start">
                            <div class="bg-red-600 text-white text-xs font-bold px-2 py-1 rounded mr-3 mt-1">YEAR 1</div>
                            <div>
                                <p class="font-bold text-slate-900">During Studies</p>
                                <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Target co-op placements in priority sectors. Take IELTS/CELPIP early and aim for CLB 9+. Network with employers who sponsor PR.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex items-start">
                            <div class="bg-red-600 text-white text-xs font-bold px-2 py-1 rounded mr-3 mt-1">YEAR 2</div>
                            <div>
                                <p class="font-bold text-slate-900">Post-Graduation</p>
                                <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Secure full-time skilled employment immediately. Register for BC PNP SIRS. Create Express Entry profile.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
